    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "My idea here is different - disconnect peers which send snap requests.\r\nWhen we are synced, we are turning off snap capability. So we can receive snap requests only when we are not synced. In this state we are useless for syncing peers, so I think we can disconnect them and both - we and them - can find more useful peers.\r\nI was testing it a bit together with eth67 + new snap healing, working fine as far, but it's still undertested",
